abstract: Study in journal Annals of Oncology reports death rate from ovarian cancer declined in United States by 16 percent from 2002 to 2012, to 4.85 per 100,000, among largest reductions in world.

headline.main: Some Good News on Ovarian Cancer

snippet: The death rate from the disease declined in the United States by 16 percent from 2002 to 2012, among the largest reductions in the world....
